# SunGenie eAnalytiX — environment template
# Copy to C:\LLM\.env (or set SUNGENIE_ENV_PATH to point elsewhere) and fill in.
# NEVER commit the real .env. These keys must be rotated — see BLOCK-03 below.

# --- LLM provider keys ------------------------------------------------------
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-google-gemini-key
NVIDIA_ISING_KEY=your-nvidia-ising-key
NVIDIA_LLAMA_KEY=your-nvidia-gemma-key

# --- Server auth (SEC-05) ---------------------------------------------------
# Shared secret required on every /api/* request. If left unset, app_server.py
# generates an ephemeral key at startup and prints it to the console.
SUNGENIE_API_KEY=generate-a-long-random-string

# --- Optional path overrides ------------------------------------------------
# SUNGENIE_DB_PATH=C:\path\to\sungenie_telemetry.db
# SUNGENIE_DATA_DIR=C:\LLM\SunGenie data

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BLOCK-03 — ROTATE LEAKED KEYS
# The previous Nvidia keys were committed to public git history (12 hits) and
# must be treated as compromised:
#   1. Revoke + reissue NVIDIA_ISING_KEY and NVIDIA_LLAMA_KEY on the Nvidia
#      developer portal, and reissue GEMINI_API_KEY if it was ever committed.
#   2. Put the NEW keys only in C:\LLM\.env (git-ignored).
#   3. Either make the GitHub repo private, or scrub history with
#      `git filter-repo` / BFG and force-push.
